========================================================================================================= 
| The following manual changes are needed the first time that we deploy the sukrupa volunteer form    ===
========================================================================================================= 

1. Create a new page in wordpress
   1. Pages -> add new
   2. Fill the tiltle of the new page as “Volunteer”
   3. Fill the content of the page with <!-- ddfm1 -->
   4. Put a space in the excerpt field.
   
2. Publish the page (click on the “publish” button)

3. Fix the volunteer anchor on Supporting Sukrupa
   1. Go to Pages (left-side menu) -> Supporting Sukrupa
   2. At the HTML field, delete the <a name="volunteers"></a> content
   3. Replace <h3>Volunteer Opportunities</h3> with <h3 id="volunteers">Volunteer Opportunities</h3>
   4. Insert <p>To volunteer with us, please fill in the <a href="http://www.sukrupa.org/volunteer/">volunteer form</a>.</p> above the text For more information, please <a href="http://www.sukrupa.org/contact/">contact us</a>.
   5. Click on the update button to publish the page


========================================================================================================= 
| Known issues                                                                                        ===
========================================================================================================= 

* Apparently the plugin does not work if the form fields use an upper case letter. Ex: fm_dayMonday

* Select fields get reset if the list of options contains spaces.
   Ex: type=select|label=...|fieldname=...|data=January, February, March, April, May, June, July...
